{title: Don’t Put Off Till Tomorrow}
{artist: The Shady Grove Band}
{composer: Written by Bill Monroe and Pete Pyle}

[G]You have no doubt in your mind
There’s a [C]heaven up [G]above
And you mean to change before the [D7]end
Till you [G]hold onto treasures
You [C]possessed here on [G]earth
Feasting your [D7]soul on [G]sin

Don’t put off till tomorrow
What [C]you can do [G]today
For tomorrow may be too [D7]late
Sinner [G]give your heart to Jesus
Won’t you [C]kneel down and [G]pray
For tomorrow may [D7]be too [G]late
You say you’ll change tomorrow
But to[C]morrow never [G]comes
These words you keep repeating day by [D7]day
How [G]sad will be the story
When you’re [C]laid in your [G]grave
In torment for[D7]ever you will [G]pay
Repeat #2
There’s a wreck on the highway
There’s [C]blood on the [G]road
That lifeless body lies [D7]cold
They’ll [G]never know Jesus
They’ve [C]waited too [G]long
They’ll never live in [D7]that heavenly [G]fold
Repeat #2